WEBVTT

00:41.041 --> 00:46.296
People might laugh
and say it's just a fairy tale.

00:46.505 --> 00:50.968
That these mysterious things
couldn't really happen.

01:28.714 --> 01:33.969
But this is the true story of my mother.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.057
The man that mother loved...

01:39.266 --> 01:41.518
Was a wolf man.

02:05.959 --> 02:11.340
Mother was a student at
a university just outside of Tokyo.

02:11.548 --> 02:13.758
Her tuition was paid for with
scholarships... this is what socrates said:

02:13.759 --> 02:15.885
- -And she worked a part-time job to cover living expenses.
- -This is what socrates said:

02:15.886 --> 02:19.446
- -And she worked a part-time job to cover living expenses.
- -In the textbook, it says...

02:20.932 --> 02:28.774
“The wise men of the world
may have great knowledge of many things...

02:28.982 --> 02:33.070
But goodness, truth, beauty, and arete... “

02:34.154 --> 02:35.530
one day in early summer,

02:35.739 --> 02:38.742
mother saw father for the
first time at the university.

02:38.950 --> 02:42.537
Wearing a shirt with a stretched-out
collar, using no textbook...

02:42.746 --> 02:45.874
Mother said he was completely
different from the other students

02:46.083 --> 02:49.836
as she watched him
from behind earnestly taking notes.

03:11.108 --> 03:12.567
Please wait.

03:17.114 --> 03:21.868
This is the attendance sheet. If you
don't turn it in, you'll be marked absent.

03:24.037 --> 03:25.414
Not a student here.

03:25.622 --> 03:26.622
What?

03:26.707 --> 03:29.835
If that bothers you, I won't come anymore.

04:08.123 --> 04:09.958
Please, wait!

04:12.043 --> 04:14.713
I don't care if you are a student or not,

04:14.921 --> 04:19.676
but the lecture can be hard
to understand without a textbook.

04:19.885 --> 04:22.304
Do you want to share mine?

04:31.396 --> 04:35.107
“Hokushin dry cleaners“

04:35.193 --> 04:39.112
it will be ready on Friday.
Thank you very much.

04:39.321 --> 04:41.031
Thank you for waiting.

05:36.670 --> 05:39.840
I'll put this here, then.

05:40.048 --> 05:42.342
I'll take this.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.854
Here, thank you.

05:54.062 --> 05:57.858
The accusers in this case
were the poet meletus,

05:58.066 --> 06:03.947
the politically powerful anytus,
and the sophist lycon.

06:04.155 --> 06:06.032
Meletus acted as their representative,

06:06.241 --> 06:09.744
but anytus is said to have
pulled the strings from behind.

06:32.183 --> 06:36.813
What do you think is fun?
What kind of food do you like?

06:37.022 --> 06:41.276
What were the people you loved
in the past like?

06:42.277 --> 06:44.779
Why are you called “Hana"?

06:44.988 --> 06:45.988
My name?

06:46.156 --> 06:47.782
Yeah.

06:47.991 --> 06:52.078
When I was born,
cosmos were blooming in the garden.

06:52.287 --> 06:55.540
They hadn't been planted by anyone,
but grew there naturally.

06:55.749 --> 06:58.752
My dad said that looking at them
made him think of my name.

06:58.960 --> 07:02.714
He wanted me to be a child
who always smiled, like the flowers.

07:02.923 --> 07:04.799
Even when things got hard,

07:05.008 --> 07:07.802
to just keep smiling,
even if the smile became forced.

07:08.011 --> 07:11.890
Because then I could
overcome most things, he said.

07:15.185 --> 07:19.689
That's why during dad's funeral,
I was smiling the whole time.

07:19.898 --> 07:25.654
But then, my relatives said that was
improper, and they were very angry with me.

07:27.739 --> 07:32.118
But... I suppose
it really was improper, wasn't it?

07:32.327 --> 07:34.079
It wasn't improper.

07:37.457 --> 07:38.959
I'm glad.

07:44.714 --> 07:51.054
“Hokushin dry cleaners“

08:00.772 --> 08:02.857
“Hakujuji“

08:05.694 --> 08:09.906
even in the same housing complex,
each room is completely different inside.

08:10.115 --> 08:16.997
Families with money, poor families,
big families, people living alone,

08:17.205 --> 08:21.584
families with babies,
elderly living alone...

08:31.928 --> 08:34.806
I bet it'd be nice to have my own house.

08:35.015 --> 08:42.022
To say, “I'm home“ and take off my shoes,
wash my face and hands, and sink into a chair.

08:42.230 --> 08:43.857
That'd be nice.

08:44.065 --> 08:45.442
I'd build a bookcase.

08:45.650 --> 08:49.446
And once that bookcase was full of books,
I'd build a new bookcase.

08:49.654 --> 08:52.866
I'd be able to do whatever I wanted
because it'd be my own house.

08:58.288 --> 09:01.499
Then, I'll say “welcome
home, “ if you want.

09:12.302 --> 09:13.762
Hana.

09:13.970 --> 09:15.847
What is it?

09:16.056 --> 09:19.350
There's something I have to tell you.

09:19.559 --> 09:21.227
You can tell me anything.

09:21.436 --> 09:22.937
Actually...

09:32.697 --> 09:34.365
I'll tell you tomorrow.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.076
Okay.

09:44.375 --> 09:50.715
“Hokushin dry cleaners“

10:01.684 --> 10:03.937
“Hakujuji“

10:04.145 --> 10:08.441
“hakujuji“
“Christmas cakes“ “western sweets & coffee“

10:19.619 --> 10:25.333
“Hakujuji“

10:32.841 --> 10:37.262
“Hakujuji“

10:40.640 --> 10:42.016
Hana.

10:44.727 --> 10:46.813
I'm sorry, Hana.

10:48.231 --> 10:50.358
I'm sorry.

10:57.490 --> 10:59.868
I've never told anyone before.

11:00.952 --> 11:02.412
I was scared.

11:02.620 --> 11:08.626
I was afraid you'd leave if I told you,
but I should have told you sooner.

11:08.835 --> 11:11.045
I should have shown you.

11:11.254 --> 11:12.338
Shown me?

11:12.547 --> 11:14.966
Close your eyes for a second.

11:21.055 --> 11:22.640
For longer than that.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.983
Can I open them yet?

12:01.179 --> 12:02.555
Hana,

12:04.098 --> 12:07.101
what do I look like to you?

12:11.439 --> 12:13.733
She found out that
transforming during the full moon

12:13.942 --> 12:18.404
and attacking people was just a legend.

12:18.613 --> 12:25.912
“The world is full of things
I don't know, “ mother thought.

12:28.081 --> 12:30.416
Were you surprised?

12:30.625 --> 12:32.252
Will you leave me now?

12:33.795 --> 12:35.421
But you're shaking.

12:35.630 --> 12:36.881
Are you afraid?

12:37.090 --> 12:38.675
I'm not afraid.

12:40.551 --> 12:42.428
Because it's you.

12:54.148 --> 12:57.568
Father was a descendant
of the honshuu wolf,

12:57.777 --> 13:00.738
which had become extinct
about a hundred years ago.

13:00.947 --> 13:05.994
With both wolf and human blood,
he was the last of his kind.

13:06.911 --> 13:12.750
When father was a child, his parents told him
about the history of his extinct ancestors.

13:12.959 --> 13:17.338
They told him not to reveal the truth
to anyone, and then died.

13:17.547 --> 13:20.758
After that, he was taken in
by relatives who knew nothing of this

13:20.967 --> 13:24.137
and had a hard time
as he grew into an adult.

13:24.345 --> 13:29.267
After getting his driver's license,
he went to the city to look for work.

13:29.475 --> 13:37.475
Unknown and unheeded by men, father
said that he had lived in hiding until now.

15:38.729 --> 15:40.207
"Natural birth: Kind to your body and soul“

15:40.231 --> 15:46.779
“hakujuji“

17:30.758 --> 17:35.137
Mother gave birth to me
in that small apartment.

17:35.346 --> 17:37.014
It was snowing.

17:37.223 --> 17:40.476
Not at the hospital,
without even a midwife,

17:40.685 --> 17:42.979
my parents delivered me by themselves.

17:43.187 --> 17:46.232
Mother was worried that
if I had been born as a wolf,

17:46.440 --> 17:51.153
the doctors would have been surprised.

17:56.450 --> 17:58.953
I'm glad she was born safely.

17:59.161 --> 18:02.623
This is just the beginning.

18:02.832 --> 18:04.834
Do you think she will be a kind child?

18:05.042 --> 18:07.420
She might be a smart kid.

18:07.628 --> 18:09.839
I wonder what kind of adult she will be?

18:10.047 --> 18:13.175
A nurse, a teacher, or a baker...

18:13.384 --> 18:15.678
Whatever it is, I want her
to have a job she loves.

18:15.886 --> 18:19.765
I want her to have a happy,
healthy life free of troubles.

18:19.974 --> 18:23.644
Let's watch over her until she grows up.

18:23.853 --> 18:25.396
Yeah.

18:40.870 --> 18:44.874
My little brother was born
in the spring of the next year.

18:45.082 --> 18:46.959
It was raining that day.

18:48.336 --> 18:52.423
Suddenly, father was nowhere to be seen.

19:39.053 --> 19:44.141
I don't know what father
was thinking that day.

19:44.350 --> 19:48.646
Maybe he instinctively went
to hunt for food for his new baby.

19:48.854 --> 19:51.065
Maybe he wanted
something nutritious for mother,

19:51.273 --> 19:53.609
who was recovering from the birth.

21:52.019 --> 21:55.940
"Driver's license“

21:56.482 --> 22:03.823
“I'm leaving the kids to you, “
mother thought she could hear him say.

22:07.868 --> 22:11.664
Leave them to me.
I'll make sure to raise them properly.

22:23.008 --> 22:28.347
Mother had a lot of trouble with us after
that, but I don't remember anything about it.

22:28.556 --> 22:29.348
Num nums.

22:29.557 --> 22:31.934
Wait a minute, yuki. I'm making it now.

22:32.142 --> 22:32.768
Num nums!

22:32.977 --> 22:33.977
I said, it's almost done.

22:34.061 --> 22:34.728
Num nums!

22:34.937 --> 22:36.188
Yuki!

22:38.023 --> 22:39.692
When I was angry or upset,

22:39.900 --> 22:43.070
my fur would bristle,
and I would turn into a wolf.

22:43.279 --> 22:47.199
Oh all right, you can have a biscuit first.

22:53.747 --> 22:55.082
Apparently, I was always hungry,

22:55.291 --> 22:59.920
crying for food from morning until night.

23:00.129 --> 23:03.465
Completely different from
my sickly brother, ame, who ate little.

23:06.135 --> 23:08.929
Mother had to quit school
and leave her part-time job

23:09.138 --> 23:11.223
in order to take care of us.

23:12.975 --> 23:15.019
That was close...

23:15.227 --> 23:20.065
We lived on the small savings
father had left behind.

23:29.700 --> 23:31.744
That was close...

23:31.952 --> 23:36.332
According to mother, my brother
and I seemed like we weren't sure

23:36.540 --> 23:41.378
if we were supposed to be humans or wolves.

23:46.550 --> 23:47.927
“Pediatric care“

23:50.095 --> 23:51.972
they got me...

23:54.224 --> 23:54.767
“Child care encyclopedia“

23:55.060 --> 23:58.145
since she couldn't ask
those around her for advice,

23:58.354 --> 24:01.315
she had no choice but to study on her own.

24:02.608 --> 24:05.194
Breastfeeding every
two hours, day and night.

24:05.402 --> 24:07.780
When ame wouldn't suck on his own,

24:07.988 --> 24:10.468
she learned to feed him
with cotton pads dipped in breast milk.

24:11.117 --> 24:15.621
“Living with wolves“

24:22.336 --> 24:25.464
But when he wouldn't
drink any milk or stop crying,

24:25.673 --> 24:27.383
she didn't know what to do

24:27.591 --> 24:30.761
except pat him on the back
and comfort him the whole night.

24:33.639 --> 24:36.725
As a result, mother was
quickly becoming exhausted.

24:44.108 --> 24:45.943
I'm okay.

24:46.151 --> 24:48.231
Thanks to this, even if it
was just for a short time,

24:48.362 --> 24:51.031
she could fall asleep at a moment's notice.

24:53.492 --> 24:54.910
Mommy?

24:55.119 --> 24:56.370
What is it?

24:59.540 --> 25:02.710
What really caused problems
was when we got sick.

25:02.918 --> 25:04.294
Yu ki?

25:05.963 --> 25:07.464
Yu ki?

25:07.673 --> 25:09.174
Yu ki...!

25:19.101 --> 25:23.313
The pediatrician or the veterinarian...
She didn't know which one to take us to.

25:23.522 --> 25:26.775
My daughter swallowed
some desiccant by mistake...

25:26.984 --> 25:28.027
She's two years old.

25:28.235 --> 25:31.530
Yes, she threw up.
There was no blood.

25:31.739 --> 25:36.952
It says “silica gel“ on it.
Um, is it dangerous...?

25:37.161 --> 25:39.121
What? Her appetite?

25:40.247 --> 25:42.207
I'm hungry!

25:43.167 --> 25:46.462
Is that so? She's okay?

25:46.670 --> 25:52.718
She regretted not asking father
about how he was raised as a child.

25:52.926 --> 25:53.677
I wanna go for a walk.

25:53.886 --> 25:54.678
Yuki, that's...

25:54.887 --> 25:55.887
Walk!

25:55.971 --> 25:58.974
You were sick just a
little while ago. So...

25:59.183 --> 25:59.892
Walk!

26:00.100 --> 26:04.313
Okay, okay.
Now, put your ears away.

26:06.732 --> 26:08.901
Okay, let's go for a walk!

26:10.194 --> 26:13.739
I said, put your ears away!

26:14.782 --> 26:15.908
Okay!

26:36.345 --> 26:38.138
Hello. Aw, how cute.

26:38.347 --> 26:40.891
He said you're cute. Isn't that nice?

26:45.270 --> 26:46.438
Oh, sorry!

26:46.647 --> 26:47.981
It's okay.

26:55.447 --> 26:57.908
But that wasn't the only problem.

27:04.498 --> 27:07.459
What time do you think it is?!
Shut him up!

27:08.919 --> 27:09.628
I'm very sorry.

27:09.837 --> 27:12.756
You keep making such
a racket night after night!

27:12.965 --> 27:14.633
I'm really very sorry.

27:14.842 --> 27:16.552
At least discipline your kids properly...!

27:20.222 --> 27:23.350
Shh... it's okay.

27:42.578 --> 27:46.915
The contract said pets
are not allowed here, didn't it?

27:47.124 --> 27:48.124
I don't have any pets.

27:48.208 --> 27:51.670
Don't lie to me.
I know what's going on.

27:51.879 --> 27:53.839
If you think you can do whatever you want,

27:54.047 --> 27:57.384
then I'll have no choice
but to have you go elsewhere.

28:00.804 --> 28:01.972
You're caseworkers?

28:02.181 --> 28:06.435
Yes, we have some serious
misgivings about your children.

28:06.643 --> 28:08.228
What do you mean?

28:08.437 --> 28:13.901
Our records show that they've
never had regular checkups or vaccines.

28:14.109 --> 28:16.612
It's all right. They're healthy.

28:16.820 --> 28:20.616
If that's the case, can
we at least see them?

28:20.824 --> 28:21.867
No, that's...

28:22.075 --> 28:23.075
Just a look will do.

28:23.202 --> 28:26.330
We just want to see if
what you're saying is true or not.

28:26.538 --> 28:27.873
You're not welcome...

28:28.081 --> 28:32.002
If you don't let us in, you could
be suspected of abuse or neglect!

28:32.211 --> 28:33.879
Please, leave!

29:14.795 --> 29:16.380
Hey...

29:16.588 --> 29:18.173
What is it, mommy?

29:18.382 --> 29:20.842
What do you want to do from now on?

29:21.051 --> 29:23.971
Do you want to be human, or wolf?

29:24.179 --> 29:25.681
Huh?

29:27.808 --> 29:29.810
I'm thinking of moving.

29:31.186 --> 29:33.772
So that you can choose
whichever one you want.

29:53.375 --> 29:55.815
Ever since the town hall
started presenting unoccupied houses,

29:55.877 --> 29:58.880
people who want to live
in the country have been coming steadily,

29:59.089 --> 30:01.133
but they never last long.

30:01.341 --> 30:03.719
As you can see, there's nothing here.

30:03.927 --> 30:06.698
The elementary school and hospital
are both thirty minutes away by car.

30:06.722 --> 30:10.100
The junior high is two and a half hours
by bus and train, one way.

30:10.309 --> 30:11.685
That's five hours round trip!

30:11.893 --> 30:15.480
No matter how much you want to raise
your children in a good environment...

30:17.232 --> 30:19.943
The town is a lot more convenient,
in my opinion.

30:34.166 --> 30:36.126
Wow...

30:36.335 --> 30:38.170
It's so big...

30:38.378 --> 30:41.006
And I know the rent is practically free,

30:41.214 --> 30:43.675
but you know, the cost of repairs
is nothing to laugh at.

30:43.884 --> 30:47.971
Instead of calling it an unoccupied
house... oh, you can keep your shoes on...

30:48.180 --> 30:51.475
It's more like an abandoned house.

30:51.683 --> 30:56.146
But at least there's electricity,
and the mountain stream isn't dried out,

30:56.355 --> 30:58.207
and they said you could use
whatever is in the shed.

30:58.231 --> 30:59.900
That's a field, isn't it?

31:00.108 --> 31:02.819
Oh, this place isn't really suitable
for growing your own food.

31:03.028 --> 31:05.947
Animals come down from the mountains
and damage the crops.

31:06.156 --> 31:09.076
Even if you make the effort
to grow vegetables, they'll all get eaten.

31:09.284 --> 31:13.372
This place is full of unoccupied houses
because the humans are getting kicked out.

31:13.580 --> 31:15.165
Then, the neighbors are...?

31:15.374 --> 31:21.713
Neighbors? There isn't anyone around for
miles. Shall we look at a different place?

31:21.922 --> 31:23.691
There might be a better
place near the village...

31:23.715 --> 31:24.424
I've decided.

31:24.633 --> 31:25.633
What?

31:25.675 --> 31:27.386
I've decided on this place.

31:29.096 --> 31:29.763
Why?

31:29.971 --> 31:32.015
Wow! What is this place?

31:32.224 --> 31:33.725
Our new home.

31:44.111 --> 31:44.736
Oopsie Daisy!

31:44.945 --> 31:46.905
It's slanted!

31:50.450 --> 31:52.494
Oh, hello Mr. Ant!

31:54.371 --> 31:56.665
Wow, what's this?!

32:02.504 --> 32:04.464
Stomp! Stomp!

32:15.142 --> 32:17.144
How is it? Do you like it?

32:17.352 --> 32:19.104
I like it!

32:19.312 --> 32:21.565
I want to go home.

32:27.863 --> 32:31.199
She said she wanted a place
with no neighbors close by.

32:31.408 --> 32:33.743
She was a little different,
if you know what I mean.

32:33.952 --> 32:34.661
What about her husband?

32:34.870 --> 32:35.412
I don't know...

32:35.620 --> 32:36.620
Her income?

32:36.705 --> 32:37.289
I'm not sure...

32:37.497 --> 32:39.958
Then how does she expect
to take care of her kids?

32:40.167 --> 32:46.089
Oh, grandpa nirasaki!
We'll be in your care from now on.

33:38.016 --> 33:39.976
Look, look! Mommy, look!

33:40.185 --> 33:41.478
Tada...!

33:46.358 --> 33:48.652
Come here, birdie...

33:48.860 --> 33:50.779
C'mon, come here...

34:14.636 --> 34:16.805
“Yuki - age 5“ “ame - age 4“

34:53.967 --> 34:55.343
Thank you very much.

34:55.552 --> 34:57.053
Thank you.

35:02.350 --> 35:03.393
Good evening.

35:03.727 --> 35:04.978
Good evening.

35:06.479 --> 35:10.317
Hey, wait, is that her?

35:16.740 --> 35:17.907
Let's go...

35:31.880 --> 35:33.506
Splash!

35:34.841 --> 35:37.010
I guess we'll have to be
more frugal from now on.

35:37.218 --> 35:38.762
Frugal?

35:38.970 --> 35:43.141
I was just thinking that we should at least
be able to grow our own vegetables.

35:44.559 --> 35:46.186
I'll help!

35:47.979 --> 35:48.979
Wait here, okay?

35:49.147 --> 35:50.440
Okay.

35:51.816 --> 35:52.859
“Home garden“

35:55.070 --> 35:55.737
these please.

35:55.945 --> 35:56.945
Okay.

35:57.113 --> 35:58.238
These, too.

35:58.823 --> 35:59.032
“The wolf is coming“

35:59.407 --> 36:00.407
oh, yuki!

36:00.700 --> 36:01.700
“The wolf is coming“

36:02.410 --> 36:06.748
it's our little secret that
you two are wolf children.

36:06.956 --> 36:07.956
Right.

36:08.083 --> 36:11.961
If you were to suddenly become wolves,
everyone would be very surprised.

36:12.170 --> 36:15.256
So you cannot become wolves
in front of other people.

36:15.465 --> 36:16.716
Promise?

36:16.925 --> 36:18.259
Promise!

36:18.468 --> 36:20.053
And one more thing.

36:20.261 --> 36:23.890
If you meet other animals in the mountains,
you can't act like you are better than them.

36:24.099 --> 36:25.266
Why not?

36:25.475 --> 36:27.769
Because daddy will feel sad about it.

36:27.977 --> 36:29.437
Okay?

36:29.646 --> 36:31.147
Okay!

36:31.564 --> 36:33.584
Iiiwe'll never forgive you! I the angry
villagers chased after the wolf with guns."

36:33.608 --> 36:36.608
"'I'm sorry! I won't do it again, '
the boastful wolf cried as he ran away."

37:02.554 --> 37:04.347
Oh no!

37:04.556 --> 37:05.556
Why?

37:05.682 --> 37:07.642
I don't know. I wonder what happened...

37:11.062 --> 37:13.064
Hello? Excuse me!

37:13.273 --> 37:14.399
What?

37:14.607 --> 37:17.652
Is it okay if I take
the fallen leaves from the woods?

37:17.861 --> 37:19.404
What did you say?

37:19.612 --> 37:21.030
The fallen leaves!

37:21.239 --> 37:24.743
No one would ask
for permission to take that stuff!

37:24.951 --> 37:26.870
Thank you very much!

37:29.122 --> 37:30.540
I wonder how long she'll last.

37:30.749 --> 37:34.669
She'll start talking about convenience
stores and karaoke soon enough.

37:34.878 --> 37:36.087
You got that right.

37:50.226 --> 37:51.895
I'll get it right this time...

37:52.103 --> 37:53.688
Mom... my...

37:53.897 --> 37:55.273
What?

37:55.482 --> 37:56.065
Ame!

37:56.274 --> 37:57.274
What happened?

37:57.400 --> 37:58.443
You calico cat!

37:58.651 --> 38:01.488
You're weak even though you're a wolf,
so they've got it in for you.

38:01.696 --> 38:03.536
They're just scratches.
Nothing to worry about.

38:03.740 --> 38:05.325
You won't be able to survive like that!

38:05.533 --> 38:06.159
Yuki.

38:06.367 --> 38:08.286
Do the “all better“ thing.

38:08.495 --> 38:09.996
All better, all better.

38:10.205 --> 38:12.624
I wouldn't lose to a wild boar!

38:12.832 --> 38:13.833
You saw a wild boar?

38:14.042 --> 38:18.171
Yup, and a monkey and a serow.
But I wasn't scared at all.

38:18.379 --> 38:20.673
It was fun when they ran away
when I chased them.

38:20.882 --> 38:21.341
And...

38:21.549 --> 38:22.549
Yuki.

38:22.717 --> 38:24.344
And then when I peed...

38:24.552 --> 38:25.720
Do you remember your promise?

38:25.929 --> 38:28.556
That you wouldn't act like
you were better than the other animals?

38:28.765 --> 38:29.349
But...

38:29.557 --> 38:30.934
Please.

38:33.186 --> 38:34.604
Fine.

38:36.064 --> 38:36.731
Thank you.

38:36.940 --> 38:40.693
Do the “all better“ thing again.

38:40.902 --> 38:43.154
All better, all better.

38:45.406 --> 38:52.288
But, how do wolf children
become adults, anyway?

38:54.749 --> 38:56.167
Yuki, wait!

38:56.376 --> 38:57.168
Piggyback.

38:57.377 --> 38:58.377
Already?

38:58.461 --> 39:00.672
You're too slow! Hurry up!

39:01.673 --> 39:05.927
“Wolves start learning to hunt
at around four months old.

39:06.135 --> 39:09.430
First, they learn what hunting is
with mice and other small animals.

39:09.639 --> 39:12.934
As they get older,
they form teams with adult wolves..."

39:13.142 --> 39:13.685
We're a team!

39:13.893 --> 39:15.019
No, we're not.

39:15.228 --> 39:16.938
Fine, be that way.

39:20.108 --> 39:21.734
Don't go too far!

39:21.943 --> 39:23.152
I know!

39:24.737 --> 39:26.072
Let's go home...

39:26.281 --> 39:32.245
Ame, I wonder if this
wild grass is edible... let's see...

39:47.594 --> 39:48.887
I got it!

39:55.476 --> 39:56.811
Got it!

40:02.650 --> 40:05.069
Oh, look at that, ame!

40:14.162 --> 40:16.080
All better, all better.

40:16.289 --> 40:20.293
Mommy, look at this! It's a cormorant!
There was a stream over there, and...

40:20.501 --> 40:22.837
Shh...

40:23.046 --> 40:24.046
Mommy...

40:25.465 --> 40:29.052
Why is the wolf always the bad guy?

40:29.260 --> 40:32.180
You mean, in the picture books?

40:32.388 --> 40:36.517
Everyone hates them,
and they're always killed in the end...

40:36.726 --> 40:40.855
If that's the case,
I don't want to be a wolf.

40:43.483 --> 40:49.447
You're right. But you know,
mommy likes wolves.

40:49.656 --> 40:55.453
Even if everyone else hates the wolf,
I'll take the wolf's side.

41:03.920 --> 41:06.798
Mommy! Mommy!

41:07.465 --> 41:08.257
What's wrong?

41:08.466 --> 41:09.467
They wilted again.

41:09.676 --> 41:10.843
What?

41:15.473 --> 41:19.477
Diseased... all of them? Don't tell me...

41:19.686 --> 41:21.688
Mommy...

41:21.896 --> 41:25.149
What's going to happen to us now?

41:29.028 --> 41:32.657
Mommy's no good like this.
I've got to learn more!

41:32.865 --> 41:34.826
Will you help me again?

41:35.785 --> 41:36.953
Sure.

41:37.161 --> 41:38.746
Thanks.

41:41.916 --> 41:42.709
Go inside.

41:42.917 --> 41:43.960
Okay.

41:44.919 --> 41:46.421
Hello!

41:46.629 --> 41:50.633
I was going to visit earlier,
but it got so busy around here...

41:50.842 --> 41:53.636
It's hard to grow your own food, isn't it?

41:53.845 --> 41:57.140
Even when I do what it says in the book,
I keep messing up.

41:57.348 --> 42:01.394
But this is a nice place, isn't it?
With nature all around us.

42:01.602 --> 42:03.146
Nature, ha!

42:03.354 --> 42:06.274
Plants don't grow overnight, you know.

42:06.482 --> 42:07.275
Huh?

42:07.483 --> 42:10.111
At this rate, it'll be the same
no matter how many times you try.

42:10.319 --> 42:11.946
Isn't that what you think?

42:12.155 --> 42:14.032
T-That's...

42:14.240 --> 42:17.201
Don't smile! Why do you smile?

42:17.410 --> 42:20.121
Even if you smile,
you won't be able to do anything.

42:35.511 --> 42:38.014
That person's scary.

42:38.222 --> 42:42.477
No, it's mommy's fault
for not knowing anything.

42:42.685 --> 42:44.812
Even though you're an adult?

42:47.023 --> 42:50.735
I should have asked
your daddy about more things.

43:02.163 --> 43:03.915
It's raining cats and dogs!

43:04.123 --> 43:05.416
Hello...

43:06.918 --> 43:08.336
Here, this is for you.

43:08.544 --> 43:09.544
What are they?

43:09.629 --> 43:10.880
Seed potatoes.

43:11.089 --> 43:13.716
You mean the ones you plant in the fields?

43:14.592 --> 43:17.345
Is there anything else
you can do with them?

43:17.553 --> 43:21.349
Don't worry about what dad said.
That's just how he is.

43:21.557 --> 43:23.893
No, it was my fault.

43:26.229 --> 43:27.897
Hello!

43:29.148 --> 43:30.233
Sorry.

43:30.441 --> 43:32.026
Don't worry about it.

43:33.361 --> 43:34.779
Here.

43:40.576 --> 43:44.455
Grandpa nirasaki,
thank you for the seed potatoes.

43:44.664 --> 43:46.958
Ah, are you trying to let them go to waste?

43:53.840 --> 43:56.175
You have to start over from the soil.

44:03.724 --> 44:05.977
You won't get anything
done hoeing like that.

44:06.185 --> 44:08.354
I'm sorry...

44:17.822 --> 44:19.574
Um, what about the fertilizer...?

44:19.782 --> 44:21.622
Did you use leaves when
you prepared the soil?

44:21.701 --> 44:22.243
Yes.

44:22.451 --> 44:23.953
Then you don't need fertilizer.

44:34.046 --> 44:36.174
When you're done, clear this field, too.

44:36.382 --> 44:41.679
I don't need such a big field. I just
need to grow enough for my kids and me.

44:43.556 --> 44:45.474
Did you hear me?

44:48.311 --> 44:49.854
Yes...

45:10.833 --> 45:12.793
Make ridges in the soil.

45:14.545 --> 45:16.297
Okay.

45:18.299 --> 45:20.218
Leave more space in between.

45:20.426 --> 45:21.928
Okay.

45:24.055 --> 45:25.890
That's too low. Make them higher.

45:26.098 --> 45:27.516
Okay.

46:07.556 --> 46:14.355
In a week, plant them cut-side down.
Don't water them. Just leave them!

46:14.563 --> 46:19.193
Um, thank you for teaching me how to...

46:35.584 --> 46:37.920
Mommy, are you okay?

46:49.140 --> 46:50.224
Hello!

46:50.433 --> 46:51.434
Come with us.

46:51.642 --> 46:51.976
Huh?

46:52.184 --> 46:53.978
It's okay, just come.

46:54.186 --> 46:54.395
What?

46:54.603 --> 46:56.355
Come on, let's go.

47:01.193 --> 47:02.194
Hey...

47:02.403 --> 47:03.821
Yes?

47:04.030 --> 47:05.790
If you plant chamomile
and cabbage together,

47:05.948 --> 47:08.284
bugs won't attack
and the flavors will be better.

47:08.492 --> 47:11.412
No, you want celery with your cabbage.

47:11.620 --> 47:13.998
No, no, it's better for
novices to use this.

47:14.206 --> 47:15.207
No, no, no,

47:15.416 --> 47:17.960
you can't fill up a stomach on chamomile.

47:18.169 --> 47:20.713
You should plant them shallowly like this.

47:20.921 --> 47:23.716
No, you should water the hole
before you put anything in.

47:23.924 --> 47:26.927
No, no, you can water them later.
Plant them first.

47:27.136 --> 47:28.679
No, no, you're wrong.

47:28.888 --> 47:31.088
You should just sprinkle
the extra fertilizer like this.

47:31.265 --> 47:33.434
If you put too much,
it'll just bring more bugs.

47:33.642 --> 47:36.145
No, give me that. You have to pile it on.

47:36.354 --> 47:38.314
No, you only need a little.

47:38.522 --> 47:40.649
If you do what this guy says,
you'll definitely fail.

47:40.858 --> 47:41.525
That's you!

47:41.734 --> 47:42.318
What?!

47:42.526 --> 47:44.195
What did you say?!

47:45.488 --> 47:46.739
Wood vinegar?

47:46.947 --> 47:49.075
It's made from the smoke
when charcoal is produced.

47:49.283 --> 47:51.827
And poultry manure.
There are instructions inside.

47:52.036 --> 47:53.913
Thank you for coming all this way to help.

47:54.121 --> 47:55.121
No, no.

47:55.164 --> 47:57.666
Sorry about showing up
without warning like this.

47:57.875 --> 47:58.542
It's no problem.

47:58.751 --> 48:01.188
It's hard working the land
if you're not used to it, isn't it?

48:01.212 --> 48:04.006
I still have a lot I have to learn.

48:04.215 --> 48:06.109
There are a lot of city folks
who get discouraged

48:06.133 --> 48:08.386
