1:01:03.702 --> 1:01:03.910
thank you.

1:01:04.327 --> 1:01:05.327
“Jobs & employment"

1:01:05.912 --> 1:01:06.912
“jobs & employment"

1:01:07.789 --> 1:01:09.082
this is...

1:01:10.417 --> 1:01:13.097
“Niikawa nature sanctuary“
“nature conservationist assistant wanted“

1:01:14.421 --> 1:01:16.464
“hometown nature“

1:01:22.387 --> 1:01:24.514
Thank you for waiting. Shall we go?

1:01:24.723 --> 1:01:27.225
My name is tendo, and I
am a nature conservationist.

1:01:27.434 --> 1:01:29.895
Welcome to niikawa nature sanctuary.

1:01:30.103 --> 1:01:32.772
I look forward to working with you.

1:01:32.981 --> 1:01:37.444
A nature conservationist's job
is not just to protect nature.

1:01:37.652 --> 1:01:41.239
Environmental education, field surveys,
the conservation of plants and animals...

1:01:41.448 --> 1:01:45.827
These three pillars of conservancy are
made possible by the support of volunteers.

1:01:46.036 --> 1:01:49.414
We do many different types of work,
so while we are specialists,

1:01:49.623 --> 1:01:52.459
we also need to be able to do
a little of everything.

1:01:52.667 --> 1:01:59.758
So, we are looking for someone who can help
the conservationist with all the work, but...

1:01:59.966 --> 1:02:05.889
Honestly speaking, we can't pay very much.
We can pay enough to cover training expenses

1:02:06.097 --> 1:02:08.017
for someone studying
to become a conservationist,

1:02:08.225 --> 1:02:10.435
but we can't afford much more than that.

1:02:10.644 --> 1:02:14.022
A high schooler's part-time job
pays a lot more per hour.

1:02:14.231 --> 1:02:16.024
Even knowing all that...

1:02:16.233 --> 1:02:18.068
Do you still want to do it?

1:02:19.486 --> 1:02:23.615
Um... I heard that you have a wolf here...

1:02:27.285 --> 1:02:29.162
This is our timber wolf.

1:02:29.371 --> 1:02:30.789
He's very quiet.

1:02:30.997 --> 1:02:32.499
He's not that young anymore.

1:02:33.541 --> 1:02:35.418
Excuse me, director...?

1:02:35.627 --> 1:02:37.254
Excuse me for a moment.

1:02:45.220 --> 1:02:48.890
Nice to meet you. I came
because I have something to ask you.

1:02:49.099 --> 1:02:50.892
He's a wolf's child.

1:02:51.101 --> 1:02:52.978
His father, the wolf, died.

1:02:53.186 --> 1:02:57.065
I'm his mother,
but I don't know how to raise a wolf.

1:02:57.274 --> 1:03:00.819
How did you learn the ways of the wolf?

1:03:03.446 --> 1:03:07.701
Will you tell us how
you were raised in the forest?

1:03:20.130 --> 1:03:21.464
Sorry about that.

1:03:23.425 --> 1:03:27.053
A wealthy person got
special permission to keep him as a pet,

1:03:27.262 --> 1:03:30.473
but when the owner died there was no one
to take him, so he came to live with us.

1:03:30.682 --> 1:03:33.768
Apparently, he was born in the Moscow zoo.

1:03:33.977 --> 1:03:35.770
So he isn't from the wild?

1:03:35.979 --> 1:03:38.815
I think it's rare to see
wild wolves in zoos.

1:03:39.024 --> 1:03:42.444
If they're bred, the babies
are sent out to be fostered.

1:03:42.652 --> 1:03:47.324
There are also wild birds and raccoon dogs
who are brought here when they get hurt.

1:03:47.532 --> 1:03:49.868
After we treat them...

1:03:52.704 --> 1:03:54.831
I'm going to start coming here from now on.

1:03:55.040 --> 1:03:57.375
Ame, you'll be okay coming with me, right?

1:03:59.169 --> 1:04:02.005
I'll learn about
the mountains and nature as I work,

1:04:02.213 --> 1:04:06.051
and teach you the things I learn.

1:04:06.259 --> 1:04:08.219
It was my first time seeing a real one.

1:04:08.428 --> 1:04:09.721
A wolf?

1:04:09.929 --> 1:04:11.723
Was daddy like that, too?

1:04:11.931 --> 1:04:13.725
No, not at all.

1:04:13.933 --> 1:04:14.933
I'm glad.

1:04:14.976 --> 1:04:16.394
Why?

1:04:16.603 --> 1:04:20.148
Because he seemed kind of sad, somehow.

1:04:22.484 --> 1:04:25.695
I wanted to meet daddy.

1:04:27.739 --> 1:04:31.826
Mommy wants to see him again, too.

1:04:32.035 --> 1:04:37.374
As mother settled into her new job,
I was undergoing a huge shock.

1:04:37.582 --> 1:04:38.917
Bunko, yours is so nice!

1:04:39.125 --> 1:04:40.543
Keno, yours is pretty, too!

1:04:40.752 --> 1:04:42.545
I found a four-leaf clover!

1:04:42.754 --> 1:04:43.754
Me, too!

1:04:43.880 --> 1:04:46.508
Yuki, did you find anything?

1:04:46.716 --> 1:04:48.510
Yeah, look!

1:04:50.387 --> 1:04:56.184
I found out that no other girls
played with rat snakes for fun.

1:04:56.393 --> 1:04:58.603
Look, these used to be my mom's.

1:04:58.812 --> 1:05:00.105
They're so pretty.

1:05:00.313 --> 1:05:02.816
My parents bought this for me
for my last birthday.

1:05:03.024 --> 1:05:04.484
Lucky!

1:05:04.692 --> 1:05:06.486
Yuki, show us your treasure box, too!

1:05:06.694 --> 1:05:07.362
Okay!

1:05:07.570 --> 1:05:08.822
Ooh, what's inside?

1:05:09.030 --> 1:05:10.240
Look!

1:05:12.158 --> 1:05:20.083
I was also the only girl who collected
small animal bones and dried reptiles.

1:05:20.291 --> 1:05:23.962
The moment I realized
that other girls didn't do those things,

1:05:24.170 --> 1:05:26.297
I was so embarrassed.

1:05:26.506 --> 1:05:28.007
Hurry up!

1:05:28.216 --> 1:05:30.343
That was when I decided.

1:05:30.552 --> 1:05:34.722
From then on, I was going to act
more graceful and ladylike.

1:05:38.977 --> 1:05:41.646
Don't laugh! I'm seriously
worrying about this!

1:05:41.855 --> 1:05:44.774
Why don't you just do what you want, yuki?

1:05:44.983 --> 1:05:47.360
I don't want people looking at me funny!

1:05:47.569 --> 1:05:49.195
I guess it can't be helped.

1:05:49.404 --> 1:05:50.697
Huh?

1:05:56.202 --> 1:06:02.500
When mother made a new dress for me,
I remember being really happy.

1:06:02.709 --> 1:06:03.334
Good morning.

1:06:03.543 --> 1:06:06.087
Thanks to the dress,
I was able to fit in with my class

1:06:06.296 --> 1:06:08.965
- -and get along with my friends.
- -Good morning!

1:06:09.174 --> 1:06:10.174
Good morning!

1:06:10.341 --> 1:06:12.260
Oh, yuki, your dress is so cute!

1:06:12.469 --> 1:06:13.553
It's wonderful!

1:06:13.761 --> 1:06:15.304
- -Lucky!
- -Heaven only knows how much that dress helped me.

1:06:15.305 --> 1:06:16.097
- -Let's go!
- -Heaven only knows how much that dress helped me.

1:06:16.098 --> 1:06:18.075
- -Okay!
- -Heaven only knows how much that dress helped me.

1:06:18.099 --> 1:06:19.099
The next year,

1:06:19.267 --> 1:06:21.811
it was hard to get ame to school.

1:06:22.020 --> 1:06:26.107
Get it? It's “piggy promise, promise kept."

1:06:27.942 --> 1:06:29.652
School's this way!

1:06:38.203 --> 1:06:42.832
“Happy first day of school!“
“1st grade“

1:06:43.666 --> 1:06:49.088
“let's get along!“ "2nd grade“

1:06:50.089 --> 1:06:55.512
“full of energy!“ “1st grade“

1:06:58.681 --> 1:07:06.681
“let's be friends!“ “2nd grade“

1:07:18.034 --> 1:07:22.622
“Please and thank you“
“3rd grade“

1:07:23.790 --> 1:07:28.670
“let's fly together!“
“4th grade“

1:07:30.046 --> 1:07:35.176
“let's figure it out!“
“3rd grade“

1:07:44.852 --> 1:07:45.895
Good morning.

1:07:46.104 --> 1:07:48.439
Oh, ame, is it a school holiday?

1:07:49.274 --> 1:07:50.024
So you're skipping?

1:07:50.233 --> 1:07:51.317
Yeah.

1:07:52.777 --> 1:07:54.696
You can come here anytime.

1:07:54.904 --> 1:07:57.574
Sorry for always bringing him here.

1:07:57.782 --> 1:07:59.385
- -Yes, this is the observation pond.
- -Ah, you're going bird-watching.

1:07:59.409 --> 1:08:03.246
- -You can see frogs that still have their tails.
- -One moment, please. You'll find it...

1:08:03.454 --> 1:08:05.516
- -Hana, can you help me for a sec?
- -...Over there on your right.

1:08:05.540 --> 1:08:06.540
Coming!

1:08:20.346 --> 1:08:21.889
Attention, everyone!

1:08:22.098 --> 1:08:25.602
Let me introduce a transfer student.
This is sohei fujii.

1:08:25.810 --> 1:08:27.353
Why don't you greet everyone?

1:08:27.562 --> 1:08:29.564
I'm sohei. Nice to meet you.

1:08:29.772 --> 1:08:31.733
Nice to meet you!

1:08:34.360 --> 1:08:36.779
Hey, do you have dogs at your house?

1:08:36.988 --> 1:08:38.573
Huh? Why?

1:08:38.781 --> 1:08:41.492
You smell kind of like animals.

1:08:43.453 --> 1:08:44.453
We don't have any dogs.

1:08:44.495 --> 1:08:48.833
Really? That's weird.
I totally thought you had dogs.

1:08:49.250 --> 1:08:50.335
What is it?

1:08:50.543 --> 1:08:52.462
Huh? Oh, the smell...

1:08:52.670 --> 1:08:54.213
Smell? What smell?

1:08:54.422 --> 1:08:57.008
Maybe it's just my imagination...

1:09:08.603 --> 1:09:10.271
Which one should I pick...?

1:09:10.480 --> 1:09:11.648
I'll go with this one!

1:09:11.856 --> 1:09:14.067
Aw man, seriously?

1:09:15.860 --> 1:09:16.986
Oh, yuki!

1:09:17.195 --> 1:09:19.864
Yuki, you should come
join us. Sohei's funny.

1:09:20.823 --> 1:09:23.034
Oh, I have to return this book.

1:09:24.702 --> 1:09:26.496
What's up with her?

1:09:26.704 --> 1:09:29.123
She's not usually like that...

1:09:29.832 --> 1:09:31.542
Hey, yuki, you know...

1:09:31.751 --> 1:09:33.419
Oh, yuki...

1:09:33.628 --> 1:09:35.588
You know what?

1:09:35.797 --> 1:09:37.006
Hey, yu ki!

1:09:37.215 --> 1:09:38.216
Yu ki...

1:09:38.424 --> 1:09:39.801
C'mon, yuki...

1:09:42.011 --> 1:09:43.638
Tell me the truth!

1:09:46.182 --> 1:09:46.933
About what?

1:09:47.141 --> 1:09:49.435
Did I do something to you?

1:09:49.644 --> 1:09:50.937
You didn't do anything.

1:09:51.145 --> 1:09:53.189
Do you dislike me
because I'm a transfer student?

1:09:53.398 --> 1:09:54.190
That's it, isn't it?

1:09:54.399 --> 1:09:55.441
I said, it's nothing.

1:09:55.650 --> 1:09:56.901
Then why are you avoiding me?

1:09:57.110 --> 1:09:58.569
I'm not avoiding you!

1:09:58.778 --> 1:10:00.571
Piggy promise, promise kept.

1:10:00.780 --> 1:10:02.573
Piggy promise, promise kept.

1:10:02.782 --> 1:10:03.991
- "Piggy...
- -Hey!

1:10:05.368 --> 1:10:06.368
Wait!

1:10:06.494 --> 1:10:07.912
Piggy promise, promise kept.

1:10:08.121 --> 1:10:09.664
Piggy promise, promise kept.

1:10:09.872 --> 1:10:11.207
Piggy promise, promise kept.

1:10:11.416 --> 1:10:13.167
Piggy promise, promise kept.

1:10:24.637 --> 1:10:26.222
Stop following me!

1:10:27.223 --> 1:10:29.100
Don't come any closer!

1:10:29.308 --> 1:10:30.518
What are you doing?

1:10:30.727 --> 1:10:32.311
Don't touch me!

1:10:32.520 --> 1:10:34.647
Yuki! Yuki!

1:10:47.785 --> 1:10:48.785
“Tsururindo“

1:10:51.122 --> 1:10:52.122
“tsururindo“

1:10:52.790 --> 1:10:53.999
“tsururindo“

1:10:55.626 --> 1:10:56.626
“tsururindo“

1:11:08.055 --> 1:11:10.433
Sorry to bother you during work.

1:11:12.727 --> 1:11:15.062
Do you know how much
his head was bleeding?

1:11:15.271 --> 1:11:16.647
It was my ear.

1:11:16.856 --> 1:11:18.149
Yuki.

1:11:18.357 --> 1:11:20.902
She wouldn't talk no matter
what we asked her...

1:11:24.655 --> 1:11:26.949
Were you really the one who hurt him?

1:11:29.619 --> 1:11:31.245
Did you apologize?

1:11:35.124 --> 1:11:36.334
Apologize.

1:11:37.502 --> 1:11:39.003
I said, apologize.

1:11:51.390 --> 1:11:52.892
I'm sorry.

1:11:54.644 --> 1:11:56.896
I'm very sorry for what my child has done.

1:11:57.104 --> 1:11:59.565
That's how it is, Mrs. Fujii.

1:11:59.774 --> 1:12:02.235
There is the school's insurance
for the medical bills, so...

1:12:02.443 --> 1:12:05.863
Do you really think this can be
taken care of with just an apology?!

1:12:07.448 --> 1:12:10.868
What were you planning to do
if he lost his hearing?

1:12:11.077 --> 1:12:13.639
Parents are responsible
for their children's actions, aren't they?

1:12:13.663 --> 1:12:16.541
Would you go into debt
or sell your house to compensate us?

1:12:16.749 --> 1:12:18.751
Now, now, this isn't the place to...

1:12:18.960 --> 1:12:22.129
If you don't let me
hear what she's thinking, I'll...

1:12:22.338 --> 1:12:23.464
A wolf.

1:12:23.673 --> 1:12:24.924
What?

1:12:25.466 --> 1:12:27.510
It was a wolf that did it.

1:12:29.595 --> 1:12:31.013
A wolf did it.

1:12:31.222 --> 1:12:32.306
Sohei?

1:12:32.515 --> 1:12:34.308
What are you saying?

1:12:34.517 --> 1:12:36.018
Soheh

1:12:36.227 --> 1:12:37.854
sohei?

1:12:38.062 --> 1:12:39.622
Don't decide whose fault it is already!

1:12:39.772 --> 1:12:40.565
I know!

1:12:40.773 --> 1:12:42.108
She's been different lately...

1:12:42.316 --> 1:12:43.526
Stop it!

1:12:48.573 --> 1:12:50.324
That's what I thought.

1:12:58.583 --> 1:13:00.376
What happened to sohei?

1:13:00.585 --> 1:13:01.752
He left early.

1:13:01.961 --> 1:13:03.045
Why?

1:13:03.254 --> 1:13:04.297
Because he got hurt.

1:13:04.505 --> 1:13:06.173
How did he get hurt?

1:13:06.382 --> 1:13:07.174
That's...

1:13:07.383 --> 1:13:09.218
Who hurt him?

1:13:11.470 --> 1:13:11.721
Yuki!

1:13:11.929 --> 1:13:13.031
- -Yuki!
- -I thought it was her.

1:13:13.055 --> 1:13:14.515
- -Thought so.
- -What's wrong?

1:13:14.724 --> 1:13:15.850
I'm like a detective...

1:13:16.058 --> 1:13:18.269
Quiet! Everyone, quiet down!

1:13:22.398 --> 1:13:24.108
It didn't work.

1:13:25.401 --> 1:13:28.613
No matter how many times I tried the charm.

1:13:30.823 --> 1:13:34.702
Will I be chased out of school?

1:13:35.578 --> 1:13:39.165
Will we have to leave our house?

1:13:41.584 --> 1:13:43.294
I'm sorry...

1:13:45.379 --> 1:13:49.133
I'm s o rryl

1:13:51.510 --> 1:13:55.097
m om, I'm sorry!

1:13:55.306 --> 1:13:57.475
All better, all better.

1:14:15.201 --> 1:14:17.161
“School bus“

1:14:39.475 --> 1:14:41.477
Sohei?

1:14:49.568 --> 1:14:52.071
Homework. From sohei.

1:15:11.048 --> 1:15:12.883
From sohei.

1:15:24.353 --> 1:15:25.980
Soheh

1:15:27.356 --> 1:15:31.193
she went to play at shino's house today.

1:15:31.402 --> 1:15:32.987
I see...

1:15:33.779 --> 1:15:35.781
Oh, wait a minute.

1:15:46.083 --> 1:15:48.252
You came a long way, didn't you?

1:15:48.461 --> 1:15:50.671
Thank you for coming by every day.

1:15:52.339 --> 1:15:55.051
I don't want yuki to stop coming to school.

1:15:57.470 --> 1:16:02.308
You know, that day,
you said that a wolf did it, right?

1:16:02.516 --> 1:16:04.518
What did you mean by that?

1:16:04.727 --> 1:16:08.147
That was... I mean...

1:16:08.355 --> 1:16:13.652
You might not believe me, but that
day, I saw a wolf for a split second,

1:16:13.861 --> 1:16:19.325
and when I came to, I was bleeding.
So the wolf was the one who did it.

1:16:19.533 --> 1:16:21.952
I mean, it wasn't yuki's fault.

1:16:22.161 --> 1:16:26.207
I know other kids
are saying stupid things, but...

1:16:26.415 --> 1:16:28.125
I see.

1:16:29.168 --> 1:16:32.046
Can I ask you one more thing?

1:16:32.254 --> 1:16:34.256
Do you hate wolves?

1:16:37.802 --> 1:16:39.678
Not really.

1:16:41.013 --> 1:16:43.390
Me neither.

1:17:03.244 --> 1:17:06.038
Hey, you wanna see this?

1:17:06.247 --> 1:17:07.373
What?

1:17:12.253 --> 1:17:14.922
It's cool, isn't it? Wanna touch it?

1:17:15.131 --> 1:17:16.674
Here.

1:17:21.846 --> 1:17:23.055
Does it hurt?

1:17:23.264 --> 1:17:24.765
It itches.

1:17:28.811 --> 1:17:30.271
Let's go!

1:17:34.150 --> 1:17:35.860
I'm going now.

1:17:36.068 --> 1:17:37.486
Where are you going?

1:17:37.695 --> 1:17:38.815
I'm going to sensei's place.

1:17:38.863 --> 1:17:40.030
Who's sensei?

1:17:40.239 --> 1:17:42.825
Sensei... is sensei.

1:17:43.033 --> 1:17:45.411
I see. Will you be okay by yourself?

1:17:45.619 --> 1:17:46.704
Yeah.

1:17:46.912 --> 1:17:47.912
Be careful.

1:17:47.955 --> 1:17:48.955
Okay.

1:17:49.039 --> 1:17:50.374
Don't stay out too late.

1:17:50.583 --> 1:17:51.876
Okay.

1:17:55.796 --> 1:17:56.797
Where's yuki?

1:17:57.006 --> 1:17:58.507
She went back to school today.

1:17:58.716 --> 1:18:00.009
Oh, that's good.

1:18:00.217 --> 1:18:01.427
What about ame?

1:18:01.635 --> 1:18:03.512
He comes and goes, I guess.

1:18:03.721 --> 1:18:05.514
That's fine.

1:18:05.723 --> 1:18:06.783
There's something to be said

1:18:06.807 --> 1:18:09.810
for a guy who stops
going to school in elementary school.

1:18:10.019 --> 1:18:11.812
Edison and I were both like that.

1:18:12.021 --> 1:18:14.101
There you go, saying such
irresponsible things again!

1:18:14.190 --> 1:18:16.233
Speaking of which,
does anyone live on the mountain?

1:18:16.442 --> 1:18:16.859
On the mountain?

1:18:17.067 --> 1:18:19.361
Ame said he was going to sensei's place...

1:18:19.570 --> 1:18:21.770
I was sure he was talking
about grandpa nirasaki, but...

1:18:21.906 --> 1:18:23.699
I don't know about that...

1:18:23.908 --> 1:18:27.369
No one would go into the mountains
during the busy farming season.

1:18:28.204 --> 1:18:30.873
Sensei knows everything.

1:18:31.081 --> 1:18:32.875
He knows everything about the mountain.

1:18:33.083 --> 1:18:36.253
I didn't think you'd make friends
with someone older than you.

1:18:36.462 --> 1:18:40.382
Bring him over to our house sometime.
I want to thank him, and...

1:18:40.591 --> 1:18:42.384
Sensei doesn't meet with humans.

1:18:42.593 --> 1:18:45.193
He doesn't come down to the village
like the wild boars and bears.

1:18:47.348 --> 1:18:50.726
But it's probably okay if it's you, mom.

1:19:06.575 --> 1:19:10.412
Sensei is the master
of the entire mountain in these parts.

1:19:12.414 --> 1:19:15.459
Thank you for always taking care of ame.

1:21:48.445 --> 1:21:50.322
“Hometown nature“

1:21:59.123 --> 1:22:02.042
“Hometown nature“

1:22:05.379 --> 1:22:07.339
you can take a bath now.

1:22:07.548 --> 1:22:09.758
Yuki, you should have
sensei teach you, too.

1:22:09.967 --> 1:22:12.469
Your hunting will get a lot better.

1:22:12.678 --> 1:22:15.180
There's a trick to running
through the forest at full speed.

1:22:15.389 --> 1:22:18.225
And to reading the terrain, too.

1:22:18.434 --> 1:22:19.935
You'll learn a lot.

1:22:20.144 --> 1:22:22.187
How to find water and
how to read the weather,

1:22:22.396 --> 1:22:25.482
and marking your territory
and getting along with others...

1:22:25.691 --> 1:22:26.900
There's no way I'm going.

1:22:27.109 --> 1:22:27.693
Why not?

1:22:27.901 --> 1:22:30.154
What about you?
Why won't you come to school?

1:22:30.362 --> 1:22:32.364
Because the mountain's interesting.

1:22:32.573 --> 1:22:34.074
Because there's a lot I don't know.

1:22:34.283 --> 1:22:35.451
I don't need to know.

1:22:35.659 --> 1:22:36.243
Why not?

1:22:36.452 --> 1:22:38.620
Just come to school already.

1:22:40.205 --> 1:22:40.747
I don't want to.

1:22:40.956 --> 1:22:41.498
Why not?

1:22:41.707 --> 1:22:42.458
Because I'm a wolf.

1:22:42.666 --> 1:22:43.459
You're a human.

1:22:43.667 --> 1:22:44.918
I'm a wolf.

1:22:49.381 --> 1:22:51.758
I've already decided not to become a wolf.

1:22:51.967 --> 1:22:53.594
Why not?

1:22:53.802 --> 1:22:54.595
Hey, why not?

1:22:54.803 --> 1:22:57.639
Because I'm human! Do you hear me?!
Because I'm human!

1:22:57.848 --> 1:22:58.891
But why?

1:22:59.099 --> 1:23:00.642
Stop asking so many questions!

1:23:00.851 --> 1:23:03.187
You're a wolf, aren't you?
Why don't you act like one?

1:23:03.395 --> 1:23:05.522
Shut up! You don't know anything!

1:23:05.731 --> 1:23:06.940
About what?

1:23:07.232 --> 1:23:09.586
If you don't come to school tomorrow,
I'll never forgive you!

1:23:09.610 --> 1:23:10.277
I'm not going!

1:23:10.486 --> 1:23:11.528
I'll never forgive you!

1:23:11.737 --> 1:23:12.779
I'm not going!

1:23:19.369 --> 1:23:20.746
Wanna fight?

1:23:21.997 --> 1:23:24.541
What is it? What's that sound?

1:23:25.792 --> 1:23:27.669
Yuki! Ame!

1:23:33.675 --> 1:23:36.345
Stop it, both of you!

1:23:50.734 --> 1:23:53.070
Stop it, yuki! Ame!

1:24:11.463 --> 1:24:12.214
Yuki...

1:24:12.422 --> 1:24:13.840
Ame...?

1:24:21.723 --> 1:24:23.433
Ame...

1:24:50.711 --> 1:24:54.506
Yuki and ame are both
starting to walk their own paths.

1:24:56.425 --> 1:25:02.139
Even though that's what I wanted...
Why am I so uneasy?

1:25:04.725 --> 1:25:07.394
Why is that?

1:25:15.944 --> 1:25:21.617
My last summer in elementary school, there
were a number of record-breaking storms.

1:25:21.825 --> 1:25:26.246
Ame started to go
into the mountains all the time.

1:25:26.455 --> 1:25:31.627
He seemed to be very worried
about the effects of the heavy rains

1:25:31.835 --> 1:25:34.087
on sensei and the plants
and animals of the mountains.

1:26:01.114 --> 1:26:02.366
Ame!

1:26:04.493 --> 1:26:06.870
Where have you been all this time?

1:26:07.079 --> 1:26:09.998
You're cold. Hang on,
I'll get the bath ready.

1:26:10.207 --> 1:26:13.794
Sensei... hurt his leg, and he can't move.

1:26:14.002 --> 1:26:16.463
He'll probably die soon.

1:26:19.800 --> 1:26:24.721
Someone has to take over all the
things he has been doing on the mountain.

1:26:28.141 --> 1:26:29.434
Ame.

1:26:30.185 --> 1:26:32.688
You can't go into the mountains anymore.
Do you understand?

1:26:32.896 --> 1:26:35.399
You're only ten years
old. You're still a child!

1:26:35.607 --> 1:26:39.486
Even if a ten-year-old wolf is an adult,
you're still...

1:26:51.915 --> 1:26:53.667
Please.

1:26:53.875 --> 1:26:56.586
Please don't go into the mountains anymore.

1:26:56.795 --> 1:27:00.215
Please... for me.

1:27:03.468 --> 1:27:05.804
C'mon! Over here!

1:27:07.389 --> 1:27:10.767
Shoot it! Pass it!

1:27:14.020 --> 1:27:15.623
- -By the way, did you know?
- -Know what?

1:27:15.647 --> 1:27:16.647
“6th grade“

1:27:18.358 --> 1:27:18.567
“6th grade“

1:27:18.567 --> 1:27:19.234
and?

1:27:19.443 --> 1:27:20.986
They said sohei's mom...

1:27:21.194 --> 1:27:22.237
Is getting married!

1:27:22.446 --> 1:27:24.030
- -What?
- -No way!

1:27:24.239 --> 1:27:25.239
Why?

1:27:25.365 --> 1:27:26.551
Probably because she's beautiful.

1:27:26.575 --> 1:27:28.785
Then sohei will have a new dad?

1:27:28.994 --> 1:27:29.703
That's good.

1:27:29.911 --> 1:27:33.206
But sohei doesn't know about this yet.

1:27:33.415 --> 1:27:34.415
What?

1:27:34.583 --> 1:27:36.793
- -No way!
- -Really?

1:27:37.002 --> 1:27:39.963
You can't tell anyone about this!

1:27:41.047 --> 1:27:44.551
All right! Yes!

1:27:44.760 --> 1:27:47.012
How many points do we have now?

1:28:39.314 --> 1:28:40.357
Good morning.

1:28:40.565 --> 1:28:42.609
Today, it will be sunny during the day,

1:28:42.818 --> 1:28:46.154
but heavy rain will start
in the evening and continue overnight.

1:28:46.363 --> 1:28:49.008
- -It's so humid!
- -Please use caution if you go out during this time.

1:28:49.032 --> 1:28:51.326
First, the meteorological report.

1:28:51.535 --> 1:28:52.535
Yu ki...

1:29:05.924 --> 1:29:09.177
- -Take care!
- -In the northwest region, it will be sunny followed by rain,

1:29:09.386 --> 1:29:12.472
with lightning in some parts.

1:29:12.681 --> 1:29:15.892
The southwest region
will be sunny followed by rain.

1:29:16.101 --> 1:29:19.271
- -Ame?
- -The northeast region will be sunny with scattered showers.

1:29:19.479 --> 1:29:23.733
- -Ame!
- -The southeast region will be sunny with scattered showers.

1:29:23.942 --> 1:29:25.902
Don't forget your umbrellas
when you go out today.

1:29:30.907 --> 1:29:35.412
So the problem is asking, how far
can the swallow fly in three hours?

1:29:35.620 --> 1:29:39.082
First of all, do you know
what seventy km/h means?

1:29:39.291 --> 1:29:40.876
If you take seventy km,

1:29:41.084 --> 1:29:43.879
km/h means the number
of kilometers traveled per hour.

1:29:44.087 --> 1:29:48.592
So in one hour,
the swallow can fly seventy kilometers.

1:29:48.800 --> 1:29:51.219
The weather front along
the sea of Japan is moving south,

1:29:51.428 --> 1:29:54.723
and atmospheric conditions
have become extremely unstable.

1:29:54.931 --> 1:29:55.931
Because of this,

1:29:56.057 --> 1:30:00.395
there will be lightning and sudden gusts
accompanying the heavy rains.

1:30:00.604 --> 1:30:04.274
Predicted rainfall is,
depending on the location,

1:30:04.482 --> 1:30:07.861
over seventy mm per hour in the flat areas,
and near the mountains,

1:30:08.069 --> 1:30:10.322
over one hundred mm per hour.

1:30:10.530 --> 1:30:14.993
The weather station has issued
a heavy rain flood warning.

1:30:15.201 --> 1:30:19.915
Use extreme caution due to possible landslides,
rises in river level, submersion of buildings,

1:30:20.123 --> 1:30:22.667
as well as other damage.

1:30:23.710 --> 1:30:27.172
And now, for today's
eleven o'clock weather alerts.

1:30:27.380 --> 1:30:32.135
In the northwest region,
heavy rain, lightning, and flood warnings.

1:30:46.524 --> 1:30:50.153
Have a seat, everyone. Sit down!

1:30:50.362 --> 1:30:52.989
It looks like there will be
severe rainstorms soon,

1:30:53.198 --> 1:30:55.241
so afternoon classes have been canceled.

1:30:55.450 --> 1:30:57.493
Yay!

1:30:57.786 --> 1:30:58.786
“6th grade“

1:31:02.916 --> 1:31:02.999
your parents are being contacted
to come pick you up.

1:31:03.208 --> 1:31:07.003
Until they come, gather in the gym
according to where you live.

1:31:27.565 --> 1:31:29.275
A blackout?

1:31:54.300 --> 1:31:55.301
I have to go.

1:32:04.102 --> 1:32:07.814
I understand. I'll head over now.

1:32:08.023 --> 1:32:11.818
Ame, let's go pick up yuki together.

1:32:12.027 --> 1:32:13.278
Ame?

1:32:17.657 --> 1:32:18.658
Ame?

1:32:18.867 --> 1:32:20.160
Where are you?

1:32:23.663 --> 1:32:24.873
Ame!

1:32:28.376 --> 1:32:29.544
Ame!

1:32:33.339 --> 1:32:34.591
Ame!

1:32:36.009 --> 1:32:37.302
Ame!

1:32:42.348 --> 1:32:44.601
Where are you, ame?!

1:32:44.809 --> 1:32:45.977
Ame!

1:33:10.460 --> 1:33:12.045
Takahiro?

1:33:12.796 --> 1:33:14.339
Mommy!

1:33:17.258 --> 1:33:19.052
Keiko!

1:33:19.260 --> 1:33:20.845
Daddy!

1:33:21.054 --> 1:33:24.766
Yankee doodle came to town... j'

1:33:30.271 --> 1:33:32.857
My parents sure are late.

1:33:33.066 --> 1:33:34.275
Don't worry.

1:33:34.484 --> 1:33:35.860
But...

1:33:36.069 --> 1:33:38.238
If we have to stay at the school overnight,

1:33:38.446 --> 1:33:39.864
we can play cards all night.

1:33:40.073 --> 1:33:41.073
Cards?

1:33:41.157 --> 1:33:42.283
I wanna play.

1:33:42.492 --> 1:33:43.868
Oh, that sounds like fun!

1:33:44.077 --> 1:33:45.370
It'll be like camp!

1:33:45.578 --> 1:33:46.972
I'll go get the cards from the classroom.

1:33:46.996 --> 1:33:48.123
Okay.

1:33:48.331 --> 1:33:50.125
Do you even know how to play cards?

1:33:50.333 --> 1:33:51.918
I only know how to play old maid.

1:33:52.127 --> 1:33:53.127
Stupid!

1:33:53.211 --> 1:33:55.088
Don't fight, you two.

1:33:56.673 --> 1:33:58.216
Shino!

1:33:58.424 --> 1:33:59.717
Oh, dad!

1:33:59.926 --> 1:34:01.344
You're so late.

1:34:01.553 --> 1:34:06.933
Sorry, sorry. It's a raging storm out
there. Yuki, we can take you home, too.

1:34:07.142 --> 1:34:09.394
Oh yeah, let's go, yuki.

1:34:09.602 --> 1:34:11.104
But...

1:34:11.312 --> 1:34:13.022
C'mon, hurry up.

1:34:13.231 --> 1:34:17.110
Thank you for offering,
but I think my mom will be here soon.

1:34:17.318 --> 1:34:18.736
You don't have to hold back.

1:34:18.945 --> 1:34:20.196
Yeah.

1:34:20.405 --> 1:34:22.907
I don't want to miss my mom when she comes.

1:34:23.116 --> 1:34:25.994
That's true. We'll leave first, then.

1:34:26.202 --> 1:34:27.202
Bye!

1:34:42.635 --> 1:34:44.137
Ame!

1:34:45.096 --> 1:34:48.266
Where are you? Ame!

1:34:48.474 --> 1:34:50.101
Ame!

1:34:59.319 --> 1:35:01.070
Ame...

1:35:01.779 --> 1:35:03.531
Where...?

1:35:18.004 --> 1:35:20.298
Sou's taking a long time.

1:35:23.009 --> 1:35:24.636
Yu ki...

1:35:32.560 --> 1:35:35.104
What, did yuki go home already?

1:35:35.730 --> 1:35:37.941
Attention everyone!

1:35:38.149 --> 1:35:40.389
We'll take everyone that's left
home in the school's car.

1:35:40.902 --> 1:35:41.902
“Emergency exit“

1:36:18.314 --> 1:36:20.316
Ame!

1:36:20.525 --> 1:36:21.776
Ame!

1:36:23.236 --> 1:36:24.529
Ame!

1:36:29.075 --> 1:36:30.410
Wait!

1:36:30.618 --> 1:36:32.996
Wait, ame!

1:37:35.600 --> 1:37:37.185
Ame...

1:37:40.980 --> 1:37:43.232
Where are you...?

1:37:58.247 --> 1:37:59.540
Why are you here?

1:37:59.749 --> 1:38:01.250
Because...

1:38:02.210 --> 1:38:03.836
You were being slow.

1:38:04.045 --> 1:38:07.548
Oh, no one's here.
Did everyone go home already?

1:38:07.757 --> 1:38:10.385
I guess we're the only ones
not getting picked up.

1:38:11.511 --> 1:38:13.888
I wonder if something happened to my mom.

1:38:16.307 --> 1:38:17.016
It's cold.

1:38:17.225 --> 1:38:18.976
Let's walk around.

1:38:21.562 --> 1:38:22.313
Yuki.

1:38:22.522 --> 1:38:24.273
Oh, wait for me!

1:38:26.859 --> 1:38:29.320
What'll we do if no one
comes to pick us up?

1:38:29.529 --> 1:38:30.988
We can just live at school.

1:38:31.197 --> 1:38:32.490
We can't do that.

1:38:32.698 --> 1:38:34.700
We can sleep in the
nurse's office at night.

1:38:34.909 --> 1:38:35.909
What about food?

1:38:36.077 --> 1:38:37.870
We can eat leftover cafeteria food.

1:38:38.079 --> 1:38:41.207
What if no one ever comes to pick us up?
Will you live at school forever?

1:38:41.416 --> 1:38:44.293
I just have to get a job.
Delivering newspapers or something.

1:38:44.502 --> 1:38:46.963
You're just a kid. No
one's going to hire you.

1:38:47.171 --> 1:38:50.174
I'll lie about my age.
I'll tell them that I'm in middle school.

1:38:50.383 --> 1:38:52.593
Do I look like a middle schooler?

1:38:57.098 --> 1:38:58.724
Really?

1:39:02.186 --> 1:39:04.063
I want to grow up faster.

1:39:08.359 --> 1:39:09.694
Me too.

1:40:32.443 --> 1:40:33.736
Ame...

1:40:33.945 --> 1:40:38.157
He's probably shivering somewhere...

1:40:38.366 --> 1:40:41.786
He's probably lost... crying...

1:40:43.663 --> 1:40:49.835
I have to... protect... him...

1:40:51.629 --> 1:40:55.925
I have to... protect...

1:41:12.441 --> 1:41:14.235
Is anyone still here?

1:41:25.997 --> 1:41:27.498
He's gone.

1:41:31.168 --> 1:41:35.840
My heart's still pounding.
Hey, why did we hide?

1:41:37.300 --> 1:41:38.801
Hey!

1:41:48.185 --> 1:41:50.021
It's like the ocean.

1:41:50.229 --> 1:41:53.190
I feel like it's going to suck me in.

1:41:53.399 --> 1:41:56.736
Will we really end up living here secretly?

1:41:57.486 --> 1:41:59.726
If our parents don't come,
then we have no choice, do we?

1:41:59.780 --> 1:42:03.200
Wh? Your mom will come for sure.
Y

1:42:03.409 --> 1:42:04.493
no, she won't.

1:42:04.702 --> 1:42:06.787
Why not? She's...

1:42:10.333 --> 1:42:13.377
My mom got married.

1:42:13.586 --> 1:42:18.799
And she's having a baby. So once
it's born, I won't be needed anymore.

1:42:21.719 --> 1:42:24.889
But she was so worried about you...

1:42:25.097 --> 1:42:27.308
I'm fine with that, though.

1:42:27.516 --> 1:42:31.437
I'll run away from home
and become a boxer or a wrestler.

1:42:31.646 --> 1:42:33.648
I'll live like a lone wolf.

1:42:33.856 --> 1:42:36.192
What do you think? Will it work?

1:42:37.443 --> 1:42:39.362
You'll be defeated in a second.

1:42:39.570 --> 1:42:41.113
You have no muscles.

1:42:41.322 --> 1:42:42.322
I'll train.

1:42:42.365 --> 1:42:44.325
I'll train and live on my own.

1:42:56.462 --> 1:43:00.800
Sou, I want to be like you,

1:43:01.008 --> 1:43:04.887
and be able to smile
even when I'm telling the truth.

1:43:19.860 --> 1:43:21.570
Sou...

1:43:21.779 --> 1:43:22.863
That day,

1:43:23.072 --> 1:43:25.866
the wolf that hurt you was me...

1:43:31.122 --> 1:43:32.623
It was me.

1:43:36.711 --> 1:43:39.338
I kept thinking that I
had to say something.

1:43:42.758 --> 1:43:45.344
It hurt to hold it in.

1:43:49.181 --> 1:43:52.601
I already knew. I knew the whole time.

1:43:52.810 --> 1:43:56.564
I didn't tell anyone your secret.

1:43:57.690 --> 1:44:01.318
I won't tell. So...

1:44:01.527 --> 1:44:03.446
Don't cry anymore.

1:44:07.867 --> 1:44:10.578
I'm not crying, these are drops of rain.

1:44:20.755 --> 1:44:22.214
Thank you.

1:44:50.201 --> 1:44:52.953
Ame... where did you go?

1:44:54.872 --> 1:44:56.290
Ame?

1:44:59.627 --> 1:45:01.670
Ame.

1:45:01.879 --> 1:45:03.380
I was looking for you.

1:45:03.589 --> 1:45:06.967
Come on, hurry back
so we can go pick up yuki...

1:45:13.891 --> 1:45:15.142
Hana.

1:45:26.862 --> 1:45:28.739
I missed you so much!

1:45:29.949 --> 1:45:32.576
It's been hard, hasn't it?

1:45:32.785 --> 1:45:33.577
I'm sorry.

1:45:33.786 --> 1:45:35.871
It's okay.

1:45:36.080 --> 1:45:39.542
I was watching you the whole time.

1:45:39.750 --> 1:45:41.293
Yeah, I know.

1:45:41.502 --> 1:45:43.754
You raised our children well.

1:45:43.963 --> 1:45:47.258
No, that's not true. I keep messing up.

1:45:47.466 --> 1:45:48.843
It's true.

1:45:49.051 --> 1:45:51.262
Yuki and ame have both grown up fine.

1:45:51.470 --> 1:45:54.181
That's not true. Because...

1:45:54.390 --> 1:45:57.893
Oh... ame...

1:45:58.519 --> 1:46:01.188
That's right. Ame's gone.

1:46:04.275 --> 1:46:05.693
Ame!

1:46:05.901 --> 1:46:07.486
Ame's fine.

1:46:07.695 --> 1:46:09.446
But...

1:46:09.655 --> 1:46:10.906
He's fine.

1:46:11.115 --> 1:46:12.908
He's already an adult.

1:46:15.578 --> 1:46:17.204
An adult?

1:46:17.413 --> 1:46:19.790
He's found his own world.

1:47:02.791 --> 1:47:04.668
Ame?

1:47:07.046 --> 1:47:08.839
Oh, ame!

1:47:13.636 --> 1:47:15.846
Are you going to leave?

1:47:18.515 --> 1:47:20.434
But...

1:47:20.643 --> 1:47:24.438
I still haven't been able
to do anything for you.

1:47:26.065 --> 1:47:28.192
I still haven't...

1:47:30.110 --> 1:47:32.112
But you're still...

1:47:43.082 --> 1:47:44.625
Wait!

1:47:47.127 --> 1:47:48.587
Ame!

1:47:50.255 --> 1:47:51.882
Ame...!

1:47:56.178 --> 1:47:57.763
Ame...!

1:48:14.613 --> 1:48:15.948
Ame...

1:48:17.908 --> 1:48:19.284
Ame...

1:48:49.023 --> 1:48:51.650
Be well...

1:48:51.859 --> 1:48:53.736
Live a good life!

1:49:14.173 --> 1:49:15.883
Goodbye.

1:49:28.312 --> 1:49:32.900
Mother said that she
would never forget that morning.

1:49:34.026 --> 1:49:38.322
The freshly washed beech leaves...
The freshly washed spider webs...

1:49:38.530 --> 1:49:41.450
The freshly washed sky...

1:49:41.658 --> 1:49:49.658
Everything glittering under the sun...
Like the world had been reborn overnight.

1:49:51.085 --> 1:49:53.879
That was what mother thought.

